The seeds.rb has some defualt data for the application like the admin user.
  * user admin@admin.com - pass adminadmin

Now it has:
	* Activities section, where you can save your activities.
	* You can save Statuses and Priorities for your activities.
	* AppConfigs for some configurations of the app.
	* Projects
	* User types for creating different types o users, like Admin, Manager, Developer and so on.
	* Home Page that shows all the user activities, activities ending on the day and late activities.
	
For the future:
	* Attach files to your activity.
	* Send message to other users.
	* Create a Projects section, where you can save your activities.
	* Create a Manager that can create projects and delegate activities to users.

This app uses:
	* Rails: >= 3.1.1
	* Ruby : >= 1.9.3-p0
	* Devise
	* Kaminari
	* Web App Theme
	
Install:
	* $ git clone git@github.com:robsonarduin/MyTasks
	* $ cd MyTasks
	* $ bundle install
	* $ rake db:create:all
	* $ rake db:migrate
	* $ rake db:seed (Creates default data, you can drop the data, just remenber to create an admin user, using the default admin, and then you can remove the default admin user)
	* $ rails s
	
